name: The Gunslinger
description:
<Transcribed from found journal, entries written in early Badlands cursive, unknown author>

SUNDAY JULY 17
Guide ran off during storm last night.  I'm now headed in the last direction he claimed Spectre City was.  Three days of water left.  I better find more soon.

MONDAY JULY 18
Made good time along a mostly intact road; 22 miles.  At sunset, could still see heat signature of something large shimmering on horizon [MISSING FRAGMENT] bodes poorly.  Camped at the remnants of an outpost.

[MISSING PAGE]

THURSDAY JULY 21
Dusk.  Back at the outpost for the fourth time.  Every time I head towards the city, by the evening, I end up here instead.  Followed the sun; I didn't circle, I didn't get lost.  This should be impossible.

[MISSING PAGES] 

insane, but a blindfold [MISSING FRAGMENT] enormous cathedral, doors wide open, made entirely of either crystal or diamond [JOURNAL ENDS]
